### Tested versions

- Reproducible in all versions between 4.3 and 4.5
- Not reproducible in: 4.2 and earlier because there was no "reset_physics_interpolation" method.

### System information

Godot v4.5.stable - Linux Mint 22.1 (Xia) on X11 - X11 display driver, Multi-window, 1 monitor - OpenGL 3 (Compatibility) - NVIDIA GeForce GTX 1070 Ti (nvidia; 550.163.01) - Intel(R) Core(TM) i7-8700K CPU @ 3.70GHz (12 threads) - 15.57 GiB memory

### Issue description

I'm creating 2D platformer with physics interpolation enabled and I want my movable platforms to teleport to path beginning instantly, without being interpolated, for this I use "reset_physics_interpolation" method.
This method doesn't seem to do anything for AnimatableBody2D, while it does work for CharacterBody2D and StaticBody2D.

### Steps to reproduce

MRP:
1. Open the project and run it;
3. Use spacebar to move bodies;
4. Notice that only lower body (StaticBody2D) teleports properly and the upper body (AnimatableBody2D) interpolates despite of "reset_physics_interpolation" being called in script.

https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f086338f-0629-4935-a386-dff3bd6889b5

Manual:
1. Enable physics interpolation in project settings;
2. Add AnimatableBody2D and StaticBody2D to scene;
3. Make short script that teleports both bodies;
4. Add "Engine.physics_ticks_per_second = 2" in "_ready" callback;
5. Run project and notice that only StaticBody2D teleports properly and AnimatableBody2D interpolates despite of "reset_physics_interpolation" being called in script.

```GDScript
extends Node2D


const LEFT :=  128.0
const RIGHT :=  1024.0


@onready var _animatable_body := $AnimatableBody2D
@onready var _static_body := $StaticBody2D


func _ready() -> void:
	Engine.physics_ticks_per_second = 2


func _physics_process(_delta: float) -> void:
	if not Input.is_action_just_pressed(&"ui_accept"):
		return

	var pos := LEFT if _animatable_body.global_position.x == RIGHT else RIGHT

	for body in [_animatable_body, _static_body]:
		body.global_position.x = pos
		body.reset_physics_interpolation()
```

### Minimal reproduction project (MRP)

[phys-interp-bug-mrp.zip](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/22602147/phys-interp-bug-mrp.zip)
